																		Re: Author Post
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3487700); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3487700&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183480" alt="Uncle Nicolini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3487700)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3487700); return false;" >Uncle Nicolini</a></span> <span class="odate time_1545098072 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Dec 2018 01:54</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4090217">
									

<p>The image from SCP-1325 is a doctored version if this <a href="http://www.flickriver.com/photos/cacaobug/2098235065/">image</a>. It's CC 2.0, so you'll be okay to the best of my knowledge.</p>
<p>EDIT: My opinions on the piece.</p>
<p>The presentation is good. I really like the menu's looks and the care that went into designing it, it's very obvious this is a passion project. The listpage module was cute, too. My only nit to pick as far as presentation goes are that it looks like the menu of a mom and pop restaurant, which Ambrose pretty obviously is not.</p>
<p>Unfortunately, I'm left a little underwhelmed by the contents of the article.</p>
<p>The menu is full of fun little anomalies, which are fun to read and don't overstay their welcome. The problem comes from the reviews at the bottom. This might be due to my ignorance, but how does the average person here know about the Foundation?<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-119997-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-119997-1')">1</a></sup> A customer threatens the restaurant by calling the full might of the Foundation on them. Somehow. There's no story being told in the reviews either, just a bunch of loosely related events happening that don't tie into anything.</p>
<p>If I had to summarize my issues with this, it would come down to 'style over substance.' It <em>looks</em> good, but ultimately is too small a serving and the taste leaves a lot to be desired.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-119997-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-119997-1')">1</a>. In a discussion with a fellow user, they mentioned the Broken Masquerade canon being a possibility here. If this is the case, I cannot tell if it was intended.</div>
</div>

